This paper deals with the problem of finding black-box adversarial examples, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision research. The paper proposes a hybrid attack strategy that combines transfer attacks and optimization-based attacks, which are both commonly used in this area. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper uses optimization techniques, which are also common in the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
